# setlistkit keeps its history clean of AI-tooling state. The ONLY AI-adjacent file that
# belongs in git is the root CLAUDE.md. Everything an assistant or its harness writes is
# session state, not source, and stays out of the tree.
#
# --- AI planning/design artifacts (generated, never source) ---
# Assistant-authored specs, architecture docs, and plans. Pages of these get
# generated per session; they are working notes, not the public project.
docs/specs/
docs/plans/
docs/design/

# --- AI / assistant harness state (never source) ---
.claude/
.omc/
.remember/
.superpowers/
.plans/
AGENTS.md
GEMINI.md
.aider*
.cursor/
.mcp.json

# --- Python ---
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
# Local virtualenvs. Rebuildable from pyproject; never in-repo.
.venv/
venv/
pyenv/
env/

# --- Test / coverage artifacts (make test) ---
.coverage
coverage.xml
htmlcov/
.pytest_cache/
.tox/

# --- State lives OUTSIDE the repo (data_root, see the design spec) ---
# A local dev data_root should never be committed even if a user points it inside the tree.
/data/
*.sqlite
*.sqlite-journal
# `slkit export tapemeasure` defaults --out to the current directory, so running it from a checkout
# drops an eighteen-megabyte generated file next to the source. It is output, never input.
/tapemeasure.json
/tapemeasure.json.partial
*.sqlite-wal
*.sqlite-shm

# --- Secrets: the setlist.fm API key file is referenced by path from config, never committed ---
*.api_key
.secrets/

# --- OS / editor junk ---
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~
.idea/
.vscode/
